20:04.829 --> 20:07.040
Klaus will know
where we can find him.

20:07.040 --> 20:09.417
One more run.

20:09.417 --> 20:11.044
One more run, then none of us

20:11.044 --> 20:13.212
have to see each other's
faces ever again.

20:15.465 --> 20:18.092
But, um, no one has found Joe?

20:19.677 --> 20:21.721
I have been looking
for Joe for years.

20:23.848 --> 20:25.934
I don't think
he wants to be found.

20:59.759 --> 21:01.886
All right.

21:01.886 --> 21:03.346
You can sit down.

21:04.347 --> 21:07.225
Well, I could have gone
to the police, Mr. Mizushima,

21:07.225 --> 21:08.434
after what happened yesterday.

21:08.434 --> 21:11.229
I don't stand for violence.

21:11.229 --> 21:15.650
This is a palace of invention,
not destruction.

21:16.651 --> 21:18.069
And I will not employ savages...

21:18.069 --> 21:20.738
Mr. Offerman, I can't
afford to lose another job.

21:20.738 --> 21:22.991
This is why I fired
the three heathens

21:22.991 --> 21:25.076
- who attacked you.
- Sir?

21:25.076 --> 21:27.578
And I'm very sorry
for what they did to you.

21:38.172 --> 21:41.092
How old were you when
they first imprisoned you?

21:42.093 --> 21:44.303
I read your file, so...

21:44.303 --> 21:45.722
Five.

21:45.722 --> 21:47.056
Five?

21:47.056 --> 21:49.183
I was in kindergarten
in San Francisco.

21:51.853 --> 21:53.855
I learned to read in the camps.

21:55.523 --> 21:57.150
"Internment camps,"
they called them.

21:58.526 --> 21:59.944
Yes.

21:59.944 --> 22:02.989
Two countries, two camps.

22:02.989 --> 22:06.159
Different in many ways,
but in the tenet, identical.

22:07.201 --> 22:09.412
To exterminate us.

22:09.412 --> 22:11.205
To extinguish our flame.

22:12.248 --> 22:14.625
Well, I see you, Joe.

22:16.085 --> 22:17.420
I see you.

22:17.420 --> 22:20.882
A young man drafted
to the front lines in Vietnam

22:20.882 --> 22:23.801
by a country that took
everything from him.

22:23.801 --> 22:25.720
No wonder your hand shakes.

22:31.100 --> 22:33.227
I wasn't drafted.

22:33.227 --> 22:34.395
I enlisted.

22:34.395 --> 22:35.730
Why?

22:35.730 --> 22:38.274
Because my father did.

22:38.274 --> 22:42.236
While we were imprisoned
in the camps...

22:43.279 --> 22:44.947
...he still served.

22:46.324 --> 22:47.700
And was killed.

22:50.244 --> 22:52.955
You know, I invited you here

22:52.955 --> 22:57.293
for more than just
to offer you an apology.

22:59.462 --> 23:03.508
I invited you here
to ask for your help.

23:03.508 --> 23:06.094
- Help?
- I recently learned

23:06.094 --> 23:11.099
that a man from my past
is still living in this world.

23:12.391 --> 23:14.018
A Nazi guard...

23:15.019 --> 23:17.814
...sadistic, cruel.

23:17.814 --> 23:19.941
And I need your help...

23:20.942 --> 23:22.902
...to find him.

23:22.902 --> 23:24.779
Why are you asking me?

23:25.905 --> 23:29.408
Because I know
a fellow forever soldier

23:29.408 --> 23:31.619
when I see one, Joe.

23:33.746 --> 23:36.874
You father fought
those monsters, too.

23:36.874 --> 23:39.001
He fought them.

23:39.001 --> 23:43.214
He fought them in France.
He fought them in Germany.

23:43.214 --> 23:44.924
He looked in their eyes.

23:44.924 --> 23:48.761
Black and cold,
the Nazi bastards.

23:51.472 --> 23:53.057
Your father died

23:53.057 --> 23:55.476
ridding the world
of this scourge, Joe.

23:56.477 --> 23:57.728
But evil is still here.

23:57.728 --> 24:00.565
You can join this struggle.

24:00.565 --> 24:03.484
A resistance against this evil.

24:03.484 --> 24:05.778
You can help.

24:07.155 --> 24:08.865
How?

24:10.825 --> 24:12.535
Enlist.

24:43.524 --> 24:48.112
We're here, amigo.

24:48.946 --> 24:50.573
<i>Ah, gracias.</i>

25:26.192 --> 25:27.652
<i>Get settled, unpack.</i>

25:27.652 --> 25:29.153
<i>Meet in the lobby at 8:00 p.m.</i>

25:29.153 --> 25:30.112
Hello.

25:30.112 --> 25:32.531
Welcome to the Hotel Palladio.

25:42.416 --> 25:45.628
This reminds me of that place
we ended up in in Rome.

25:45.628 --> 25:47.255
When you got us lost.

25:47.255 --> 25:48.673
No, we weren't lost. I just...

25:48.673 --> 25:51.884
You just wanted to show me
the real Rome. Uh-huh.

25:51.884 --> 25:53.511
Look, on the main streets

25:53.511 --> 25:55.388
we'd been mobbed by
the Flash fanatics.

25:55.388 --> 25:56.722
On the back streets...

25:56.722 --> 25:58.641
...it was just us.

25:59.809 --> 26:03.771
Come on, you had fun.
Don't deny it.

26:05.523 --> 26:07.149
The pizza was good.

26:13.614 --> 26:15.157
I'll see you tonight.

26:16.701 --> 26:18.035
Yeah.

26:38.306 --> 26:40.057
Look pretty tonight, boy.

26:43.185 --> 26:44.937
You should knock first.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.990
Do you never even think
about Spain?

26:56.991 --> 26:58.868
About what you did?

27:02.621 --> 27:04.790
I think about that boy
every day.

27:05.791 --> 27:08.044
I see him every day.

27:12.214 --> 27:14.133
I'll see you at 8:00.

27:30.149 --> 27:33.277
<i>♪ Well, I know
it's kinda late ♪</i>

27:33.277 --> 27:35.988
<i>I hope I didn't wake you ♪</i>

27:35.988 --> 27:38.407
<i>♪ But what I got to say...</i>

27:45.748 --> 27:47.333
<i>♪ 'Cause every time
I tried to tell you...</i>

27:47.333 --> 27:49.001
<i>Hi, you've reached
Sam's message service.</i>

27:49.001 --> 27:50.753
Bonjour, Jacques.

27:50.753 --> 27:52.338
It's your love.

27:52.338 --> 27:54.882
My twat of a fiancé
has bolted the coop,

27:54.882 --> 27:58.928
so why don't you come over
and give me what he never could?

28:01.055 --> 28:03.641
Oh, I hope Israel
is wonderful, Sam.

28:03.641 --> 28:06.602
I'm just sat over here
sweating my balls off,

28:06.602 --> 28:08.771
preparing for my interview
with Professor Oughourlian.

28:08.771 --> 28:11.774
I don't miss you at all,
by the way.

28:12.983 --> 28:15.653
Call me. Love you.

28:15.653 --> 28:17.238
<i>Tried to tell you ♪</i>

28:17.238 --> 28:19.824
<i>♪ The words just come
out wrong ♪</i>

28:19.824 --> 28:23.327
<i>♪ So I'll have to say
I love you ♪</i>

28:23.327 --> 28:25.329
<i>In a song ♪</i>

28:37.716 --> 28:39.635
"1430...

28:39.635 --> 28:41.512
Harper Avenue...

28:41.512 --> 28:43.431
Los Angeles...

28:47.268 --> 28:49.186
Millie"?

28:56.444 --> 28:59.238
- Meyerleh.
- Look at you.

29:00.239 --> 29:01.782
<i>Shalom,</i> Simon.

29:01.782 --> 29:03.409
It's hard to believe it.

29:03.409 --> 29:05.911
<i>Shalom,</i> indeed.

29:05.911 --> 29:07.997
How has so much time passed?

29:07.997 --> 29:09.874
The last time I last saw you

29:09.874 --> 29:12.334
was at Ethel Shteinberg's
wedding.

29:12.334 --> 29:15.045
And tomorrow starts her shiva.

29:15.045 --> 29:17.089
- No.
- That's how long

29:17.089 --> 29:18.591
- we've been out
of each other's lives.
- Yeah.

29:18.591 --> 29:21.135
- But you're a busy man, Simon.
- No.

29:21.135 --> 29:24.805
What? Taking on Friedrich
Peter and his Freedom Party

29:24.805 --> 29:26.432
- was no small feat.
- Well,

29:26.432 --> 29:28.142
I don't believe
a man responsible

29:28.142 --> 29:31.437
for the extermination
of 13,000 Jews in Ukraine

29:31.437 --> 29:34.356
is deserving of leading
Austria into a new era.

29:34.356 --> 29:35.566
- Bravo, my friend.
- No!

29:35.566 --> 29:37.860
Please, please.
I just do God's work.

29:37.860 --> 29:40.029
- A prophet stands before me.
- No, no, no prophet.

29:40.029 --> 29:41.071
A patsy.

29:41.071 --> 29:42.281
Come, come, my friend. Sit down.

29:42.281 --> 29:44.408
Yes, of course.

29:44.408 --> 29:48.287
Scott said that you needed
to see me right away.

29:48.287 --> 29:49.580
Well...

29:49.580 --> 29:52.666
I saw... him.

29:52.666 --> 29:54.752
Right on 79th Street.

29:54.752 --> 29:56.545
Getting into a car.

29:56.545 --> 29:57.671
Saw who?

29:57.671 --> 29:59.340
Viktor Frondheim.

29:59.340 --> 30:01.634
- Viktor Frondheim?
- Yes.

30:02.635 --> 30:04.929
- Sounds familiar.
- I remember him
from the camps.

30:04.929 --> 30:08.349
He was an SS guard on Block 11.

30:08.349 --> 30:12.228
If any Jews managed
to escape, they sent him,

30:12.228 --> 30:14.772
and he always came back
with them in his jaws.

30:14.772 --> 30:16.690
Dead.

30:16.690 --> 30:19.026
Like he was a bloodhound.

30:19.026 --> 30:20.819
So tell me, um...

30:20.819 --> 30:22.905
do you have any idea
where he might be going?

30:24.156 --> 30:27.910
Connecticut... I think,
because the car had, uh,

30:27.910 --> 30:30.663
- Connecticut plates.
- Hmm.

30:31.789 --> 30:33.499
Maybe you have
information on that?

30:33.499 --> 30:36.085
Somewhere? Perhaps I can see it?

30:36.085 --> 30:39.880
Perhaps something
that I could be helpful with?

30:40.923 --> 30:45.469
No, no, no. I'm very grateful
for the offer, but no.

30:45.469 --> 30:48.556
I-I would never put you
in that position.

30:48.556 --> 30:50.724
I can't have a prince
doing yeoman's work.

30:50.724 --> 30:52.059
Oh, no, please.

30:52.059 --> 30:53.686
I will take it from here.

30:54.979 --> 30:56.438
So...

30:56.438 --> 30:58.732
thank you for the tip,
my friend.

30:59.775 --> 31:02.319
I will take care of it.
How about that?

31:02.319 --> 31:03.862
You would do that for me?

31:03.862 --> 31:04.947
Of course.

31:04.947 --> 31:08.492
Oh, you are blessing
from Hashem.

31:08.492 --> 31:10.119
Meyer, for you, anything.

31:10.119 --> 31:12.079
- Oh.
- Please.

31:12.079 --> 31:14.039
And if you do happen
to see this, uh,

31:14.039 --> 31:15.833
Viktor Frondheim again,
do let me know.

31:15.833 --> 31:17.585
Of course.

31:17.585 --> 31:19.461
The prophet.

31:22.214 --> 31:23.591
Be well, my friend.

31:23.591 --> 31:24.925
Mazel tov.

31:37.438 --> 31:41.358
Scott, see if we have a file
on a Viktor Frondheim.

31:45.821 --> 31:47.573
Hold the elevator.

32:05.716 --> 32:08.719
Just as you said.
And the other file's there, too.

32:08.719 --> 32:10.596
Well done.

32:10.596 --> 32:11.972
Here.

32:12.973 --> 32:14.892
For your troubles.

32:15.893 --> 32:18.103
I wasn't drafted into this.

32:18.103 --> 32:19.480
I enlisted.

33:45.983 --> 33:50.279
I mean, I am dying to know.

33:51.739 --> 33:53.240
What did they do to you?

33:53.240 --> 33:56.201
Because you have undergone
a real transformation, friend.

33:58.495 --> 34:01.290
My parents
tried to rehabilitate me, too.

34:01.290 --> 34:04.042
I saw a social worker,
did therapy,

34:04.042 --> 34:05.502
repented, cried.

34:05.502 --> 34:08.338
Hell, I praised Jesus so much...

34:13.802 --> 34:16.847
...and a lot of love,
a man can change.

34:17.848 --> 34:19.641
But it didn't really take.

34:19.641 --> 34:20.726
So...

34:22.561 --> 34:25.063
Between pals, I'm just asking...

34:26.231 --> 34:28.150
...you faking?

34:29.693 --> 34:31.111
You can tell me.

34:32.321 --> 34:34.031
I'm a vault.

34:40.871 --> 34:42.289
She's over there.

35:09.233 --> 35:10.943
I failed you
in New York.

35:12.945 --> 35:14.446
So why bring me here?

35:16.448 --> 35:19.409
Take off your boots.
They're filthy.

35:33.131 --> 35:34.842
When I first
saw Adolf,

35:34.842 --> 35:38.303
I was just a child
and he was a...

35:38.303 --> 35:39.596
god.

35:41.056 --> 35:42.391
An eagle...

35:43.851 --> 35:47.145
...who soared on golden wings
above all the Earth.

35:50.399 --> 35:52.442
Your trousers are muddy.

35:52.442 --> 35:54.319
Take them off.

35:54.319 --> 35:57.531
He groomed me when I was
still a child, 17.

35:58.740 --> 36:00.826
I was a gymnast.

36:02.119 --> 36:03.328
Accomplished.

36:04.329 --> 36:05.622
He liked that.

36:07.833 --> 36:09.251
Your shirt.

36:14.548 --> 36:15.966
I remember

36:15.966 --> 36:18.719
our first night together
in his apartment in Munich.

36:19.761 --> 36:22.055
I crawled into bed with him.

36:23.390 --> 36:25.017
The eagle.

36:26.059 --> 36:29.271
And... uh, he was no god.

36:30.606 --> 36:31.899
He was...

36:33.442 --> 36:34.902
...small and...

36:36.320 --> 36:38.572
...pasty, and...

36:38.572 --> 36:42.409
balding, and sweaty,
and pathetic.

36:42.409 --> 36:45.454
But all the rest of them,
they still see the eagle.

36:45.454 --> 36:46.955
They don't see me.

36:47.956 --> 36:49.708
I sent for you
because you see me.

36:49.708 --> 36:51.251
You always have.

36:52.502 --> 36:54.338
And I deserve to be seen.

37:00.552 --> 37:02.679
He can't fathom
the way forward anymore.

37:03.680 --> 37:05.432
I can.

37:05.432 --> 37:08.560
I know how we can retake power.

37:11.229 --> 37:13.231
Clean yourself off.

37:28.997 --> 37:30.791
Now we can finally begin...

37:31.792 --> 37:33.335
...my way.

37:48.684 --> 37:50.644
<i>It's showtime.</i>

37:50.644 --> 37:53.355
<i>We find Klaus Rhinehart,
we find Hitler.</i>

37:56.274 --> 37:59.194
<i>Klaus will have his guards
watching him.</i>

37:59.194 --> 38:02.280
<i>We take them out,
then Millie will take Klaus.</i>

38:15.252 --> 38:17.254
Boss says you can take a break.

38:52.289 --> 38:54.124
Here you are, sir. Number 88.

40:37.227 --> 40:38.186
Hello?

40:54.077 --> 40:57.080
<i>¿Ochenta y ocho?</i>

40:57.080 --> 40:59.624
<i>Sí.</i>

41:38.830 --> 41:41.082
Come on, you're on.

41:41.082 --> 41:42.918
Don't touch me.
What are you doing?

41:42.918 --> 41:46.463
Hey, hey. Wait. What?
Hey. No, no, no, no, no.

41:46.463 --> 41:49.549
Whoa, hey! Hey! Hey, come on!

41:56.681 --> 41:57.641
Oh, shit.

43:48.835 --> 43:49.836
Put it down.

44:07.228 --> 44:08.646
Run.

44:11.191 --> 44:13.526
I've been looking
for you, Klaus.

44:54.526 --> 44:56.569
<i>Gute Nacht,</i> motherfucker.

45:04.411 --> 45:06.413
Nazi fuck!

45:19.175 --> 45:20.552
What's in it and who's it for?

45:20.552 --> 45:22.137
I don't know.

45:25.140 --> 45:27.851
- Where are you taking it?
- Fuck you!

45:27.851 --> 45:29.477
Tell me
or you're a dead man.

45:29.477 --> 45:30.520
Who's it for?

45:30.520 --> 45:31.771
Ah!

45:59.799 --> 46:02.260
Moron.

46:06.848 --> 46:08.349
Drop the gun, Jonah.

46:08.349 --> 46:10.477
What the fuck
are you doing, Harriet?

46:11.478 --> 46:14.230
- I said drop the fucking gun.
- What the fuck are you doing?
